
This drawer contains technical information for programmers.  You will need to
use a SHELL to access the information contained here.  The following items
are included:

1. psound.library

   This is an AmigaDos sharable library that allows 'C' and assembly language
   programmers to read data from the Perfect Sound hardware.


2. voice.c

   This 'C' program will perform speaker dependant voice recognition.
   On the test data provided (6 words) the recognition rate is 100%.  The
   program uses a simplified version of a method that has been shown to have
   an accuracy of 97%.  The routine is not real time. Commented source and
   executable are included.

ALL PROGRAMS IN THIS DRAWER ARE COPYRIGHT 1990 ANTHONY J. WOOD

